How to run jupyter notebook from remote server Step1 : Start jupyter notebook in remote server #
nohup jupyter notebook &ndash;no-browser &ndash;port=8889 Step2 : Connect from remote server # ssh -N -f -L localhost:8889:localhost:8890 remote@remote_ip
Show running jupyter notebook # jupyter notebook list
Select column from data frame using lapply lapply(list, &ldquo;[&ldquo;, c(1:4,10)) &hellip;

